  "decision_conditions": [
    "This Beech is located within the back garden of 1 Green Lane. The tree presents a mature and attractive crown, which is highly visible from both Green Lane and properties in Rickmansworth Road.",
    "The tree has a high amenity value, thereby making a significant positive contribution to the local landscape.",
    "The crown of this Beech is characterised by its shape with weeping, pendulous branches. The proposed work will considerably lessen the height and spread of this appeal tree and reduce the contribution to the character and appearance of the area.",
    "No arboricultural report has been supplied justifying the proposed works, which would make the tree appear excessively cut back, significantly damaging its weeping appearance and increasing the risk of dieback, potentially impacting on the long-term health and useful life expectancy of the tree.",
    "Having regard to the reasons given for the proposed work, the work is unnecessary, unjustified and will have a detrimental impact on the visual amenit",
    "The removal of deadwood, dangerous / hanging branches and ivy:  This does not require the formal consent of the Council.",
    "Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981:  Note that it is an offence under this act to disturb roosting bats, nesting birds or any other protected species."
